name: @nessdevelopment8779
text: To add backup on your analogy with cloud migration, I'm a ten-year senior Java enterprise developer working for the Defense Department. And I'm on the cloud migration team where we are JUST NOW comparing different CSPs before we even start migrating! Lord only knows how long the actual migration will take, but I'm guessing at least a few years. AND on your other analogy about COBOL, about 1/3 of our developers are COBOL programmers maintaining our central mainframe. :-D So yes, there will always be some old mess in legacy systems moving at glacial speed. Not everything is on the cutting edge. Now the old messes aren't a lot of fun to work on compared to the new sexy stuff, but they're certainly not eliminated. It's still a decent paycheck.
